## EVAPORATOR INSPECTION  


1. Remove the cooling unit. (Refer to 07-11 COOLING UNIT REMOVAL/INSTALLATION.) 
2. Remove the evaporator from the cooling unit. 
3. Inspect for cracks, damage, and oil leakage. If any are found, replace the evaporator.  


4. Inspect for bent fins. If any are bent, use a flathead screwdriver to straighten them.